  "texts": [
    "A modified version of this construction can be carried out for a set Q ⊂ R d which is, say, open.",
    "In this case, the space of potential currents (those for which the potential norm is finite) would consist of those metric currents, that have only a controlled \"explosion\" at the boundary of Q and therefore, in general, the space of potential currents cannot be expected to coincide with all metric currents.",
    "This justifies the naming convention.Theorem 3.14.",
    "The space P d is an isometric closed subspace of C(K), therefore it is a separable Banach space.Proof.",
    "The fact that P d is an isometric subspace of C(K) follows from Theorem 3.12."
